<HEADLINE>
<P>
PUTTING THEIR STAMP ON AN UNFORGETTABLE MOMENT IN COMPTON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nat King Cole's daughter Casey Cole, above, unveils a stamp honoring her 
father Friday at Compton College.The city had proclaimed it Nat King Cole/Ethel 
Waters Day. The ceremony, which included Roger Hamilton Spotts, right, playing 
music Cole made famous, was part of a nationwide monthlong salute to these 
artists, plus Ethel Merman, Bing Crosby and Al Jolson. The five singers are 
commemorated in the U.S. Postal Service's Legends of American Music series. 
</P>
</TEXT>
