<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; COUNCIL 
ACTS TO END 5 DWP MANAGERS' OVERTIME PAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles City Council took steps Friday that could end overtime 
payments to five of the Department of Water and Power's highest-paid managers. 
</P>
<P>
 A proposed ordinance would give legal authority to a DWP board resolution 
approved in April to disqualify the managers from such pay. 
</P>
<P>
 In March, a report revealed that 468 managers who earn more than $70,000 a 
year each received an average of $4,600 in overtime payments in 1992. In 
contrast, employees who work in other city departments and have annual salaries 
of $55,000 apiece averaged about $745 in overtime compensation. 
</P>
<P>
 The DWP board voted to discontinue the overtime pay for two assistant general 
managers, the chief financial officer and two executive assistants to the 
general manager. They earn $114,000 to $150,000 a year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
