<TEXT>
<P>
 Jury Awards $28.6 Million for Asthma Drug Damage: The award went to a man who 
suffered brain damage after using a common asthma drug made by Key 
Pharmaceuticals Inc., a subsidiary of Schering-Plough Corp. of Madison, N.J. 
Paul R. Bocci III, 24, lost his short-term memory ability as a result of a 
toxic reaction to the drug, Theo-Dur. According to evidence at a trial in 
Portland, Ore., Key Pharmaceuticals sold the drug without adequately informing 
doctors about problems associated with its use. Schering-Plough criticized the 
verdict and said it plans to appeal. 
</P>
