<HEADLINE>
<P>
NITTY-GRITTY: INSIDE & OUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times-Washington Post News Service 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Before returning an opened ice cream carton to freezer, cover ice cream 
surface with a sheet of foil or plastic wrap. This will prevent ice crystals 
from forming. 
</P>
<P>
 * Scour tree sap from windows with a damp paper towel that has been dipped in 
baking soda. It is less abrasive than scouring powder. Windows will sparkle 
when wiped dry with soft cloth. 
</P>
<P>
 * If you're having a party and are short of serving trays, try using baskets. 
An assortment of sizes can hold everything from hamburger rolls to fried 
chicken. 
</P>
<P>
 * If your shower or tub is cluttered with soap, shampoo and conditioner 
bottles, store in a plastic hanging flower pot hooked over shower-head or 
curtain rod. Water will drain from holes in bottom of pot. 
</P>
