<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: VAN NUYS; FUNDS TO PREVENT NEW FLOOD AT COLLEGE OKD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Faulty water pressure regulators that caused flooding at Valley College will 
be repaired, thanks to a measure approved this week by the Los Angeles 
Community College District. 
</P>
<P>
 The district's board of trustees voted unanimously to authorize $30,000 to 
replace eight water pressure regulators. The contract, passed under emergency 
resolution, was awarded to Levko Plumbing Co. 
</P>
<P>
 On Aug. 11, two water pressure regulators failed at the Van Nuys community 
college, causing utility tunnels to flood. The water level in the tunnels rose 
to within an inch of electrical transformers. 
</P>
<P>
 The work is expected to be completed during the Labor Day weekend in order to 
prevent failure of the temporary repairs and to avoid endangering the electric 
transformers again. JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
</TEXT>
