<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: GLENDALE; BUSINESSMAN WINS $100,000 IN LOTTERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KAY HWANGBO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lady Luck smiled upon a Glendale businessman Friday, when he won $100,000 in 
the lottery. 
</P>
<P>
 "I feel great," said Serjik Gholi, who said he could hardly believe his good 
fortune."Once I receive the check I will believe it." 
</P>
<P>
 Gholi's lucky scratcher ticket, purchased at an Alpha Beta Market in Glendale, 
made him eligible to play the Big Spin game on Friday. The 34-year-old selected 
two matching squares from a game board, which allowed him to spin the big money 
wheel. 
</P>
<P>
 A flick of the wrist netted him $100,000 -- the fourth-largest amount on the 
wheel. 
</P>
<P>
 The owner of a business that sells fire-sprinkler systems, Gholi said his 
immediate plans are to take family and friends out for a celebration dinner. 
Next, he said, he will help his parents buy a house, and buy himself a car to 
replace one that was stolen two weeks ago. 
</P>
<P>
 Gholi will receive a lump-sum check for about $72,000 after taxes. KAY HWANGBO 
</P>
</TEXT>
