<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: NEWBURY PARK ; ACTRESS PLEADS NOT GUILTY TO 
MOLESTATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 45-year-old Newbury Park pornography actress charged with sexually molesting 
a 14-year-old boy pleaded not guilty in Ventura County Superior Court on 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Laurie Arden, charged with six felony counts of child molestation, was given a 
trial date of Oct. 3. 
</P>
<P>
 Prosecutors say Arden had sex with the boy in April and May after she hired 
him to help her move out of a rented room in a house on White Oak Lane in 
Newbury Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Arden allegedly showed him nude images of herself on a computer screen and in 
a magazine, then suggested they have sex. 
</P>
<P>
 A Municipal Court judge ordered Arden to stand trial in the case last month 
after listening to the boy recount the sexual encounters during a preliminary 
hearing. 
</P>
<P>
 The defendant is charged with two counts of unlawful sexual intercourse with a 
minor, two counts of sexual conduct using a foreign object, one count of 
showing explicit photos to a minor and one count of lewd and lascivious conduct 
with a minor. 
</P>
<P>
 The boy testified that he agreed to have sex with the woman the first time 
because he was "curious and confused." 
</P>
<P>
 He said they had sex a second time after Arden threatened to report him to 
police. 
</P>
<P>
 Arden is being held in the Ventura County Jail in lieu of a $20,000 bail. 
DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
</TEXT>
