<P>
BASEBALL STRIKE: DEVELOPMENTS FROM DAY 22 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Games lost: 15. 
</P>
<P>
 * Total games lost: 284. 
</P>
<P>
 * Games remaining: 385. 
</P>
<P>
 * Total income lost by players: $97.2 million. 
</P>
<P>
 * Estimated revenue lost by owners: $187 million. 
</P>
<P>
 * Key development: None and no negotiating session is scheduled. 
</P>
<P>
 * In quotes: "Baseball had been the emblem of the national pastime, the emblem 
of kids, the symbol of summer. It is now unfortunately becoming a symbol of 
national greed." 
</P>
<P>
 -- Robert Reich 
</P>
<P>
