<P>
LACK OF INTELLIGENCE SEEN AS THE KEY ISSUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I think it is appalling that The Times published a story on a college football 
player who, by his own stupidity, negligence and callousness, blew off his left 
hand in an explosion caused by a bomb he made ("Touching Back -- Payam Saadat 
Returns to Football After Losing Left Hand in Explosion," Aug. 29). 
</P>
<P>
 Instead of reading Poor Man's James Bond, Saadat should have looked for a book 
entitled, Poor Man's Guide to a High IQ. 
</P>
<P>
 HOWARD COHEN 
