<HEADLINE>
<P>
BEST BETTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE BOEHM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bette Midler had plenty to say Thursday about Orange County, Irvine Meadows 
Amphitheatre and Laguna Beach, where she owns a house: 
</P>
<P>
 * "Orange County at last. It's only taken me 20 years to get here.Well, time 
flies when you're on Prozac." 
</P>
<P>
 * "Irvine Meadows Amphitheatre in the middle of (nowhere). It has always been 
my ambition to play next to a water slide." 
</P>
<P>
 * "I'm an eco-warrior. I'm the queen of 'Save Laguna Canyon.' . . . (In 
Laguna,) the whole city recycles, so I'm very proud to be a part of that city. 
. . . I have a house down here. I don't like to tell all my Democratic 
friends." 
</P>
<P>
 * "I shot (the 1988 film) 'Beaches' down at Crystal Cove, one of the most 
beautiful beaches in the world." MIKE BOEHM 
</P>
</TEXT>
