<P>
WEEKEND TV; A HOLIDAY LINEUP FILLED WITH FOOTBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By N.F. MENDOZA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The holiday's sports lineup kicks off today with a college football 
doubleheader on ABC. At 12:30 p.m. USC opens the season with the Washington 
Huskies at the Coliseum, on Channels 7, 3, 10 and 42.Then, UCLA and Tennessee 
meet at the Rose Bowl at 5 p.m. on the same channels. 
</P>
<P>
 On Sunday, the 1994 NFL season begins, with games to be televised on NBC, Fox 
and TNT. 
</P>
<P>
 Open-minded golf and tennis fans will find two tournaments on the tube: For 
netters, there's the U.S. Open today at 11 a.m. on CBS (Channels 2 and 8) and 
4:30 p.m. on cable's USA. Sunday's matches begin at 9:30 a.m. on CBS and 
continue at 4:30 p.m. on USA. 
</P>
<P>
 For duffers, the third round of the Milwaukee Open tees off today at 10:30 
a.m. on ABC, and the final round gets under way Sunday at 3 p.m. N.F. MENDOZA 
</P>
