<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOLIDAY CLOSINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Monday is Labor Day. The following will be closed in observance of the 
holiday: 
</P>
<P>
 * All city, county, state and federal offices. 
</P>
<P>
 * County, state and federal courthouses. 
</P>
<P>
 * City and county libraries. 
</P>
<P>
 * Banks and savings and loans. 
</P>
<P>
 * Schools: All school offices and campuses, including those at colleges and 
universities, will be closed.  
</P>
<P>
 * Mail: There will be no mail delivery. All post offices will be closed, and 
mail deposited in mailboxes will be picked up according to the posted holiday 
schedule. 
</P>
<P>
 * Trash: There will be no trash pickup by city or county refuse workers. Trash 
pickups will be a day late throughout the week in unincorporated areas of the 
county and in most cities, with the exceptions of Anaheim, Fullerton and 
Orange. In those cities, residents with normal trash collection on Monday 
should put their trash out for Tuesday pickup; everyone else in those cities 
will be on regular schedule. 
</P>
<P>
 * Buses: Orange County Transportation Authority buses will run on the Sunday 
holiday schedule. There will be no dial-a-ride or car-pool services available. 
</P>
<P>
 * Parks: All city- and county-run parks and recreation facilities will be open 
during regular hours. 
</P>
</TEXT>
