</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Residents will be allowed to hold garage sales this weekend for the first time 
since an ordinance regulating them went into effect, a city spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Code enforcement officials will be out today and Sunday to ensure that the 
sales meet city guidelines designed to keep them orderly, said Bruce Dunams, 
coordinator for community preservation. 
</P>
<P>
 Under the ordinance, approved earlier this year, residents may hold garage 
sales only during the first weekends of March, June, September and December. 
Anyone holding a sale outside the four sanctioned weekends risks a fine and 
will have the goods confiscated, pending a hearing.JON NALICK 
