<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUPLE FOUND IN HOME DIED OF GUNSHOTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police investigating the deaths of an elderly couple found in their home said 
Friday that each appeared to have died from a single gunshot to the head. 
</P>
<P>
 Police and coroner investigators found a revolver in the bedroom with the 
victims Thursday evening after they entered the house in the 200 block of East 
Wilson Street, police said.There was no sign of forced entry, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The man has been identified by police as James Arthur Mayhew, 79. 
Identification of the 64-year-old woman was being withheld Friday pending 
notification of her next of kin. 
</P>
<P>
 Neighbors have identified the residents as husband and wife who had lived in 
the neighborhood for 25 years. 
</P>
<P>
 The husband, they said, was a retired Marine Corps pilot, and the couple had 
met and married in Japan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
