<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN LEAPS TO HIS DEATH AT DISNEYLAND HOTEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man in his 70s apparently jumped to his death Friday from the ninth floor of 
the Bonita Tower at the Disneyland Hotel, a Disneyland spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities found two notes on the man's body, according to John McClintock, 
one in Chinese and a briefer one in English, directing that a relative in 
Southern California be contacted by phone. 
</P>
<P>
 The man was staying at another part of the hotel, McClintock said, having 
checked in alone Thursday. He apparently plunged from a fire escape landing 
near a bank of elevators, landing on the roof of a first floor lobby. To get to 
the landing, McClintock said, the man had to climb over a railing. 
</P>
<P>
 Anaheim police are investigating the death. 
</P>
