<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; UC IRVINE WOMEN OPEN VOLLEYBALL SEASON WITH VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Denise Dumble set a UC Irvine match record with seven aces as the Anteaters 
beat Southwest Missouri State in three games in the opening round of the 
Anteater women's volleyball tournament Friday at Crawford Hall. 
</P>
<P>
 Popi Edwards and Stacy Mitchell each had 11 kills as UC Irvine won, 15-4, 
15-8, 16-14, in the season-opener for both teams. 
</P>
<P>
 Dumble, a transfer from Bakersfield College, passed the mark of six aces set 
in 1988 by Kim Collins against Northern Illinois. 
</P>
<P>
 Missy Clements, a former standout at La Habra High, had 21 kills as Cal State 
Northridge rallied to beat Fresno State, 13-15, 8-15, 15-3, 15-6, 15-13, in the 
other match. 
</P>
<P>
 UC Irvine plays Cal State Northridge at noon and Fresno State at 7 p.m. today. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Concordia Labor Day Volleyball Festival: 
</P>
<P>
 Concordia and Southern California College advance -- The Eagles and Vanguards 
each won twice in pool play to advance to the championship bracket. Concordia 
beat Cal State Hayward, 8-15, 15-8, 9-15, 15-12, 15-13, and Cal State Dominguez 
Hills, 15-8, 15-17, 15-10, 15-2. Southern California College beat Christian 
Heritage, 15-6, 15-2, 15-3, then swept Whitworth, 15-7, 16-14, 15-13. 
</P>
<P>
 In the San Diego Tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Central Florida 3, Cal State Fullerton 0 -- Lisa Fa'agata had nine kills but 
Cal State Fullerton lost, 15-13, 15-9, 15-5, in its season opener. Michelle 
Cutright had nine kills for Central Florida (1-1). 
</P>
