<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: CSUN RALLY NETS WIN OVER FRESNO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Missy Clements had 21 kills and Aimee Stone added 15 as the Cal State 
Northridge women's volleyball team rallied from a two-game deficit to defeat 
Fresno State in the opening match of the UC Irvine Invitational on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 The scores were 13-15, 8-15, 15-3, 15-6, 15-13. 
</P>
<P>
 Heather Anderson added 12 kills, 16 digs and eight blocks in the Matadors' 
season opener. Stephanie Pfau added eight kills and a match-high 10 blocks. 
</P>
<P>
 Northridge plays Irvine today at noon and Southwest Missouri State at 5 p.m. 
Football 
</P>
<P>
 Sherdrick Bonner, former Cal State Northridge quarterback, completed a 25-yard 
touchdown pass to Calvin Schexnayder with 31 seconds remaining to give the 
Arizona Rattlers a 36-31 victory over the Orlando Predators in the ArenaBowl on 
Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Bonner completed 25 of 38 passes for 267 yards and four touchdowns with one 
interception. 
</P>
</TEXT>
