<P>
 Most coaches would experience at least a few sleepless nights following the 
graduation of a talent such as Stanford freshman Chris Draft--The Times 1993 
Orange County back of the year. But not Marrujo, who has made a career of 
keeping the Tigers' football machine at full strength by developing the right 
replacement parts. "Chris was great, but he's gone now and you just have to 
move on," Marrujo said. "We've had a lot of good players leave before and we've 
always managed to be pretty competitive." Don't count on any changes this 
season. Marrujo has enough talent to win his 11th league title in 14 seasons, 
and the Tigers should again compete with Savanna and Western for the top spot. 
Marrujo expects the defense to be among the league's best--and with good 
reason. Gray, first-team all-league as a sophomore and junior, dominates at 
defensive back. And he's faster and stronger this season. Reilly, first-team 
all-league last season, is fierce against the run. SCHEDULE 
</P>
