<P>
 Carter, an Anaheim assistant for three seasons, takes over after the two-year 
reign of Todd Borowski, who twice guided the Colonists to the Southern Section 
Division VI playoffs. Carter played tailback at USC from 1971-75; you can 
probably guess his offensive preference. And thanks to Reuben Droughns, Anaheim 
might have the top rushing offense in Orange County. As a sophomore, Droughns 
gained 2,039 yards and scored 18 touchdowns, and was chosen Cal-Hi Sports 
sophomore player of the year. Anaheim's success, however, is not contingent on 
Droughns' legs alone. Carter expects the Colonists' defense to win some games, 
too. Reuben's brothers, Robert Droughns and Nowden, are integral parts of the 
defense. SCHEDULE 
</P>
